@page "/how-enigma-works"

<SeoHead Title="How Enigma Works | Puzzle Maze Gameplay Guide"
         Description="Understand how Enigma runs work, how puzzle rooms behave, how rewards are earned, and what happens when a maze is abandoned."
         OpenGraphType="article"
         SchemaType="Article"
         Keywords="how Enigma works, puzzle maze gameplay, Enigma guide, maze run rules" />

<div class="content seo-page-shell">
    <section class="panel seo-page-hero">
        <span class="profile-kicker">Guide</span>
        <h1>How Enigma Works</h1>
        <p>Each Enigma run starts with a generated or saved maze seed. From there, the player moves room to room, solves locks, gathers rewards, and reaches the finish room before leaving or failing the run.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="panel seo-page-section">
        <h2>Run Flow</h2>
        <h3>Start a Maze</h3>
        <p>Players generate a new maze or load an existing saved map. Before entry, they can select items and choose whether to run in fullscreen or windowed mode.</p>
        <h3>Solve Rooms</h3>
        <p>Rooms can use direct stage interactions or console-based overlays. Some puzzles are solved entirely in the room, while others open through the console with the `E` key.</p>
        <h3>Finish or Lose</h3>
        <p>Runs are permanent. Leaving a real maze counts as a loss, and successful completion awards Maze Nuggets and progress.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="panel seo-page-section">
        <h2>Rewards and Progress</h2>
        <h3>Maze Nuggets</h3>
        <p>Completing rooms, collecting rewards, and finishing runs contributes to a player’s Maze Nuggets total.</p>
        <h3>Saved Maps</h3>
        <p>New discoveries can become persistent maps with their own art, market value, and leaderboard history.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="panel seo-page-section">
        <h2>FAQ</h2>
        <h3>What happens if I leave a maze?</h3>
        <p>Leaving a real run ends it permanently and records the run as lost.</p>
        <h3>Do all puzzles use the console?</h3>
        <p>No. Some puzzles are solved directly in the room with movement and interaction, while others use the console overlay.</p>
        <h3>Can I replay saved maps?</h3>
        <p>Yes. Saved maps can be loaded again, replayed, rated, and traded if you own them.</p>
    </section>
</div>
